## Structured Architecture

The user confirmed everything was OK to proceed.

The architecture was drafted as:

- Hybrid module: steward agent plus formalized lifecycle workflows.
- The steward owns the canonical model.
- Lifecycle workflows create and refine artifacts with formalization built in.
- Automated reasoning adapters invoke configured tools.
- Formal companion artifacts expose rigorous English explanations, exports, validation, repair proposals, and provenance by source artifact.

Memory/model state structure was proposed:

```text
_bmad/formally-bmad/
  canonical/
    model/
    ontology/
    temporal/
    meta/
    versions/
    status.md
  artifacts/
    brainstorming/
    prd/
    architecture/
    epics/
    stories/
  exports/
  reports/
  provenance/
  indexes/
  tool-runs/
```

Memory contract included:

- `canonical/model/`
- `canonical/ontology/`
- `canonical/temporal/`
- `canonical/meta/`
- `canonical/versions/`
- `canonical/status.md`
- `artifacts/<source>/`
- `provenance/`
- `tool-runs/`
- `reports/`
- `indexes/`

Cross-agent interaction:

1. Lifecycle workflow edits source artifact.
2. Workflow proposes formal delta and rigorous English companion.
3. Steward validates delta.
4. On pass, steward commits delta, provenance, status block.
5. On ambiguity/contradiction, workflow asks questions or proposes repairs.
6. Accepted repairs edit affected BMad artifacts and canonical model.
7. Explicit contradiction overrides mark the model inconsistent.

